briefTitle: Lung-MAP: AZD4547 as Second-Line Therapy in Treating FGFR Positive Patients With Recurrent Stage IV Squamous Cell Lung Cancer
officialTitle: A Phase II Study of AZD4547 for Previously Treated FGFR-Positive Patients With Stage IV Squamous Cell Lung Cancer (Lung-Map Sub-Study)
conditions: Stage IV Squamous Cell Lung Carcinoma AJCC v7
summary: This phase II/III trial studies how well FGFR inhibitor AZD4547 (AZD4547) works in treating patients with stage IV squamous cell lung cancer that has come back after previous treatment. This is a sub-study that includes all screened patients positive for the fibroblast growth factor receptor (FGFR) biomarker. FGFR can cause tumor cells to grow more quickly. AZD4547 may decrease the activity of FGFR and may be able to shrink tumors.

primaryOutcome.measure: Objective Response Rate (Confirmed and Unconfirmed, Complete and Partial)
primaryOutcome.timeFrame: From date of registration to maximum of 2 years and 4 months or death.
